 deterministic setup might benefit from the entries the driver can apply before generation. It seems important to include dependencies that the normal usage documents state are necessary, like doxia-module-apt and doxia-module-xdoc. I should also consider maven-default-skin. I’ll gather all relevant documentation by searching for resources, including javadocs and Maven Doxia Sitetools documentation. It's crucial to ensure I have everything needed for proper setup!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IaMXWLwPUvs6uEggkpOLoBdv|fc_06f5a8a96b1bc899016a3f87c9df34819590ad9f5bee167ef1", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nurls=[\n 'https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia-sitetools/doxia-site-renderer/index.html',\n 'https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia-sitetools/doxia-site-renderer/dependencies.html',\n 'https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia-sitetools/doxia-site-renderer/usage.html',\n]\nfor u in urls:\n print('---',u)\n try:\n  data=urllib.request.urlopen(u,timeout=10).read().decode('utf-8','ignore')\n  for line in data.splitlines():\n   if any(s in line.lower() for s in ['description','site renderer','dependency','doxia-module', 'skin', 'parser']):\n    print(line[:240])\n except Exception as e:\n  print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7009, "output": 552, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46985, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782548418576, "responseId": "resp_06f5a8a96b1bc899016a3f87c350748195ac86b61b514a6389"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_IaMXWLwPUvs6uEggkpOLoBdv|fc_06f5a8a96b1bc899016a3f87c9df34819590ad9f5bee167ef1", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "--- https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia-sitetools/doxia-site-renderer/index.html\n | Generated by Apache Maven Doxia Site Renderer 2.0.0 from src/site/markdown/index.md.vm at 2026-03-31\n | Rendered using Apache Maven Fluido Skin 2.1.0\n    <meta name=\"generator\" content=\"Apache Maven Doxia Site Renderer 2.0.0\" />\n    <title>Introduction – Site Renderer</title>\n      <li><a href=\"index.html\">Site Renderer</a><span class=\"divider\">/</span></li>\n    <li><a href=\"../doxia-skin-model/skin.html\">Skin Descriptor</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"dependency-info.html\">Maven Coordinates</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"dependency-management.html\">Dependency Management</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"dependency-convergence.html\">Dependency Convergence</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"../../../skins/index.html\">Skins</a></li>\n<h1>Doxia Sitetools - Site Renderer</h1>\n<p>The Site Renderer handles the rendering of sites, assembling a common site template (also called <em>a skin</em>) with a collection of documents.</p>\n<p>Documents can be dynamically generated with <a href=\"/doxia/doxia/doxia-sink-api/\">Doxia Sink API</a>, like Maven reports, or simply read from static files written in <a href=\"/doxia/references/index.html\">markup supported by Doxia Parse\n<p><img src=\"doxia-site-renderer.png\" alt=\"\" /></p><section><a id=\"Doxia_Site_Skins\"></a>\n<h2>Doxia Site Skins</h2>\n<p>A default site template is included (see <code>default-site.vm</code>), but other templates can be used at will, either as a standalone template or packaged in a <a href=\"../doxia-skin-model/\"><strong>skin</strong> artifact</a>.</p>\n<p>Maven team provides <a href=\"/skins/\">a collection of skins</a> for projects use.</p>\n<p>Some documentation is available on <a href=\"/plugins/maven-site-plugin/examples/creatingskins.html\">how to create a new skin</a>.</p></section><section><a id=\"Velocity_processing\"></a>\n<th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<td>The version of the Doxia Site Renderer in use.</td></tr>\n<th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<p>Additionally, there are <a href=\"https://velocity.apache.org/tools/3.1/tools-summary.html\" class=\"externalLink\">Velocity Generic Tools</a> populated with the site locale, the site model's date format, and site renderer's resource bundle:\n<th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<p>If you intend to use custom Velocity tools, add them to the Maven Site Plugin's dependency list and make sure that they have a bundled configuration file in <code>/META-INF/maven/site-tools.xml</code>.</p>\n<th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<p>When Velocity is processing the site template (be it from skin or local template), there are a few complementary variables available that give access to information taken from document being merged into the template:</p>\n<th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n--- https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia-sitetools/doxia-site-renderer/dependencies.html\n | Generated by Apache Maven Doxia Site Renderer 2.0.0 from org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-project-info-reports-plugin:3.9.0:dependencies at 2026-03-31\n | Rendered using Apache Maven Fluido Skin 2.1.0\n    <meta name=\"generator\" content=\"Apache Maven Doxia Site Renderer 2.0.0\" />\n    <title>Project Dependencies – Site Renderer</title>\n      <li><a href=\"index.html\">Site Renderer</a><span class=\"divider\">/</span></li>\n    <li><a href=\"../doxia-skin-model/skin.html\">Skin Descriptor</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"dependency-info.html\">Maven Coordinates</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"dependency-management.html\">Dependency Management</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"dependency-convergence.html\">Dependency Convergence</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"../../../skins/index.html\">Skins</a></li>\n<td><a class=\"externalLink\" href=\"https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia/doxia-modules/doxia-module-xhtml5/\">doxia-module-xhtml5</a></td>\n<td><a class=\"externalLink\" href=\"https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia-sitetools/doxia-skin-model/\">doxia-skin-model</a></td>\n<td><a class=\"externalLink\" href=\"https://maven.apache.org/doxia/doxia/doxia-mo